criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age >18 years, any sex;

          -  Patients who underwent elective open or laparoscopic rectal resection ostomy
             construction (loop/end ileostomy; loop/end colostomy) for either oncological and
             Inflammatory Bowel Disease (IBD) indications;

          -  Normal water contrast enema prior to surgery;

          -  Both neo-adjuvant and adjuvant treatment are allowed for cancer patients;

          -  Both immunosuppressant and biological medications are allowed for IBD patients.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients age at screening < 18 years;

          -  Pregnant or breastfeeding women;

          -  Neurodegenerative disorders or psychiatric diseases;

          -  Contraindications or hypersensitivity to the use of the investigational product or its
             components;

          -  Patients with skin features (e.g., tattoos, pre-existing scarring) which could
             interfere with the study assessments;

          -  Patients with post-operative bleeding (to be assessed 24 hours after surgery).
